Lunch was okay. 
It is stated on the door that dinner cheque is accepted. At checkout unfortunately it is not accepted under the heading that it is only valid for dinner. Supposedly on the website , which is not true .

reviews.title: Special surprise
reviews.text: A particularly pleasant surprise next to our holiday park. Nice ambience, friendly and pleasant staff, very nice. Felt at ease. Delicious drinks with a board you say you to, compliment for the kitchen. Freshly made - and regional products Good flavours, finely matched.  Recommended and within walking distance of holiday park. Next holiday is our food and drink address, this address.

tips.body:
BEN JE OP DE VAKANTIEPARKEN IN DE BUURT , LAAT JE VERRASSEN DOOR DIT FIJNE RESTAURANT.
Heerlijke kaart van prima producten .

reviews.title: Lovely and a nice place
reviews.text: Dinner with my sister at Fusion tonight. Unfortunately there wasn't much to do, but that didn't spoil our fun. The food was delicious, the ambiance fine and the service very friendly and attentive. At a quick holiday in the Sheepfold we will definitely be back!!

reviews.title: Loveless buffet
reviews.text: I hadn't been here before but we were supposed to have an organized buffet here with a couple of acquaintances. After a game of miniature golf we were put at small loose tables at which it was difficult to eat. The chairs had a hard edge so it was not really comfortable to eat. The buffet was in a word terrible. It wasn't coordinated and seemed to come straight out of the freezer. There was no love in it and downright outrageous to charge 30 euros per person without dessert. For this we had to pay 3.50 extra per person and again the same: a large bowl with balls of ice cream croaked in it and whipped cream. Well, enjoy your meal. There was nothing to it! I don't know how the food is a la cart but I'm definitely not coming back here.

tips.body: Wanneer het niet lukt om een buffet te organiseren, doe dit dan niet. Er zijn nog zoveel opties mogelijk, nu is het een ware teleurstelling.

reviews.title: Nice location....great food.
reviews.text:
We'd been here before. Now at the new Owner also good food. 
The atmosphere is cozy and the staff is super friendly.

reviews.title: Nor very good nor bad, but the place is nice!
reviews.text: Vandaag 14 september hebben wij hier gegeten. Mijn wortelsoep was lekker en broodje groentekroket goed. Echter mijn vrouw kreeg veel te zoute kippen - groentesoep en de veel te flauwe omelet was zwart verbrand. De plek is leuk om te zitten als de overijverige grasmaaier niet tijdens, maar voor de lunch het minigolfterrein had gemaaid. Aan de ene kant dus een positieve feedback, aan de andere kant een negatieve. Hierdoor kan ik het eethuis noch aanraden noch afraden. Helaas want in principe is het leuk. For English see below.Today, 14 September, we ate here. My carrot soup was tasty and vegetable croquette sandwich good. However, my wife got much too salty chicken - vegetable soup and the much too bland omelette was burnt black. The place is nice to sit if the overactive lawn mower had not mowed the mini golf course during, but before lunch. So, on one hand a positive feedback, on the other a negative one. As a result, I can neither recommend nor reject the restaurant. Unfortunately, because in principle it is nice.

reviews.title: Best experience ever
reviews.text:
(For English scroll down) 

Ik ben niet zo'n recensist maar voor Wissel maak ik een uitzondering. Wat een belevenis. Zelden nog nooit zo lekker gegeten, goeie porties en zeer smaakvol. De zalm werd perfect op wens gebakken en de vegetarische opties waren super! 

Heerlijke plek en super vriendelijk en betrokken personeel. We waren er unaniem over eens dat we eigenlijk alles opnieuw wilden beleven. Komen zelf uit Gouda maar zouden de 1.5 uur rijden overwegen om hier weer te eten. 

---------------—--------

I am not a review writer but for this restaurant it's more than worth it. The 4 of us had the same feeling, we wanted to RE experience the taste again. The combinations, the ambiance was amazing. Lovely place to sit and lovely staff.

Food was so great, salmon was perfectly baked as wished, steak was superb, vegetarian options were amazing. Desert was to die for. We all had different picks. From the boeren Yoghurt to chocolate cake. You'd eat your fingers with it if you don't watch out.

10/10 would visit again! Even worth the 1.5 hour trip!

reviews.title: Most amazing food ever!
reviews.text: Best food we've had in a long time. What a joy to eat here. Friendly staff, AMAZING foods. Went out to eat with 4 friends, we all agreed we wanted to enjoy this food for the first time all over again. Be aware, after you've eaten here, other restaurants will disappoint you!

reviews.title: Excellent hosts, fine details
reviews.text: Excellent hosts, fine details in the surrounding. Even in the pouring rain they make sure the terras looks nice from inside. The food taste very good from the main course to the garnishes. Temperature, atmosphere, flexibility...I did encounter everything. Well done, will recommend and return. The cheese platter was divine.

reviews.title: Very nice, very good
reviews.text: We had the "keuzemenu". 3 courses for a fixed price. The food was very good and very creative. The ambiance is very cozy.

reviews.title: Nice landscape, but a bit of deception about the food
reviews.text: The area is beautiful. Green, calm and relaxing. Restaurant has a very friendly staff, no complains at all. All of them kind and gentle. But the food was really disappointing. It was a tasting menu. You take a pice from the buffet of what you want. I didn’t like the seasons, and in fact some of the options were really bad flavor, unfortunately. Maybe another try in the future is worth.

reviews.title: Cycling from hulshorst then lunch at wissel
reviews.text:
We enjoyed a beatiful cycletrip from our summerhouse at bad Hoophuizen to Wissel
Wissel offers great food inside and on their terrace
If you like to play midget golf you can enjoy the very well maintained green

reviews.title: We had an awesome dinner
reviews.text: With a group of friends I went to the Veluws Eethuis Wissel. We went there with a groupon so it was pretty cheap but normally it is prized alright. Around 25€ for a three course dinner. I had baked mussels and fish, and the taste was really amazing. I had creme brulee as a dessert and it was the best I ever had. If you have a chance to go there do that!

articleContent.title: How many days in Lisbon is enough?

seoInfo.metaDescription: You could see Lisbon in two days. But here’s why you’ll want more—and what to do if you’ve got the time.

Yes, two days in Barcelona is just enough time to eat loads of tapas, head to the beach, and take in all the Gaudi architecture you can handle. In other words, you can hit all the highlights. You'll get a real feel for this Catalan city and its spirit—those sunny afternoons drinking cava, late dinners on cobblestone squares, and nights where you can dance until dawn.

Berlin is nothing if not resilient, having outlasted many turbulent periods in its history. Those scars still show today in the stark distinction felt between the east and west sides of the city even though it’s been decades since the Berlin Wall came down. And for a European capital city, it’s not conventionally beautiful like Paris or London. Instead, Berlin embraces its eccentric hodgepodge of grit and glamour.
